TRACK 2   System of AI Engine   AI / ML Engineering 
Problem Statement 
Build a stateful trading psychology  coach that reasons across sessions   -  with a verifiable memory 
layer and a reproducible  evaluation harness.  The hard part is not calling an LLM. It is building a 
memory system that is accurate  (no hallucinated  references  to trades that never happened),  queryable 
(the system must explain why it said what it said), and persistent  across server restarts. You are 
building infrastructure,  not a chatbot. 
 
Seed Data 
File: nevup_seed_dataset.json  -  10 synthetic trader profiles structured  as nested JSON with 
ground-truth  pathology labels.  You must use this file as-is. The evaluation  harness must be 
reproducible  from this exact dataset. Do not modify or regenerate  it. 
 
Memory Contract  -  Expose All Three Operations 
Reviewers  will call these endpoints directly during evaluation.  They must match this contract  exactly. 
 
// Persist a session summary after a session ends PUT /memory/{userId}/sessions/{sessionId} body: { summary: string, metrics: BehavioralMetrics, tags: string[] } 
 // Query memory for context before generating a coaching message GET /memory/{userId}/context?relevantTo={signal} response: { sessions: SessionSummary[], patternIds: string[] } 
 // Retrieve a specific session for hallucination audit GET /memory/{userId}/sessions/{sessionId} response: raw session record (must exactly match what was stored) 
 
Hard Requirements 
# Requirement Detail 
1 Behavioral  Profiling Ingest a trader's  history from the seed dataset and produce a 
structured  profile. Each claim (weakness  pattern, failure mode, 
peak window) must cite the specific sessionId  and tradeId from 
which it is derived. Generic statements  with no evidence are a 
grading failure. 
2 Session-Level 
Interventions 
Given a stream of sequential trades via POST /session/events, 
detect any of the 5 behavioral  signals from Track 1 and generate  a 
contextual  coaching message.  Latency: <= 3 seconds p99 on 
warm, repeated calls. Cold-start  timing does not count. 
3 Anti-Hallucination 
Audit 
Coaching  responses that reference prior sessions must cite real 
sessionIds.  Implement POST /audit: accepts  a coaching response 
body and returns  each referenced  sessionId  with a found | not-
found flag. Reviewers will call this endpoint. 
4 Memory 
Persistence 
The memory store must survive a docker compose  restart without 
data loss. In-memory stores (plain Python dicts, non-persisted 
Redis) that reset on restart fail this requirement. 
5 Evaluation  Harness Using the 10 provided trader profiles,  run your coaching system 
and produce a classification  report showing  precision, recall, and 
F1 per pathology  class. Include the script  -  reviewers will run it 
from scratch. 
6 Streaming 
Responses 
Coaching  messages must stream token-by-token  via SSE or 
WebSocket.  A single blob after 3 seconds is worse UX than a 
stream that starts within 400ms. 
 
