Row-Level Tenancy Rule 
The single most important auth rule  -  applies to all three tracks 
The sub claim (userId) in the JWT must exactly match the userId in the data being accessed. 
Any mismatch must return HTTP 403  -  never 404. 
Returning  404 or 200 instead of 403 is an automatic  point deduction. 
 
if (jwt.sub !== requestedUserId) {   return HTTP 403 { error: 'FORBIDDEN', message: 'Cross-tenant access denied.' } } 
 
Reviewers  will run an automated  test: (1) issue a JWT for User A, (2) request User B's data using User 
A's token, (3) expect  HTTP 403. 
 
